---
import Base from "../../layouts/Base.astro";
---

<Base
  title="Anxiety & Overthinking · Ennea Evolution"
  description="The worry isn't random. It's guarding something. There's nothing wrong with you, and there's a way through this."
>
  <div style="--accent:#56B6B1;">
    <!-- PANEL 1 · white · hero -->
    <section class="panel">
      <div class="container narrow">
        <p class="eyebrow">Personal Work</p>
        <h1>The worry isn't random. It's guarding something.</h1>
        <p class="lead">Everyone keeps telling you to stop overthinking, as if there's a switch you've been refusing to flip.</p>
        <p>You've tried the switch. You've also rehearsed tomorrow's conversation tonight, start to finish, twice, with revisions. You know it doesn't help. You'll run it again anyway.</p>
        <p>So before anything else, here's what I want you to know: there's nothing wrong with you, and there's a way through this. I've walked it with a lot of people. The worry has a reason, and the reason is the way out.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- PANEL 2 · tint #E9F3F1 -->
    <section class="panel tint-band" style="--tint:#E9F3F1;">
      <div class="container narrow">
        <h3>You might recognize this</h3>
        <ul class="marklist">
          <li>The mind that races ahead, rehearsing what could go wrong and replaying what already did.</li>
          <li>The replay after every room, certain you said the wrong thing.</li>
          <li>The low hum of unease when nothing is even wrong, which is the part that's hardest to explain to anyone.</li>
          <li>The worry that stopped being a thought a while ago and now just lives in your chest, your gut, your shoulders.</li>
        </ul>
        <p style="margin-bottom:0;">Different faces. Every one of them is trying to protect you from something.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- PANEL 3 · white -->
    <section class="panel">
      <div class="container narrow">
        <h3>There's a way through this</h3>
        <p>You've tried arguing with the worry. It doesn't argue back. It just waits, and it's more patient than you are.</p>
        <p>So we do something different. We stop fighting it and get curious about it.</p>
        <blockquote class="pullquote">A worry that gets fought grows. A worry that gets understood loosens its grip.</blockquote>
        <p>And once you can see what it's been guarding, you get a say in the matter. That's the new part. Up until now, it's been deciding for you.</p>

        <h3 style="margin-top:2.5rem;">What changes</h3>
        <p>The energy comes back. All the energy that went into scanning and bracing is yours again.</p>
        <p>You still have hard things to do. They just stop feeling so enormous. An email can be an email. A decision can be a decision. A day can ask things of you without taking the whole room.</p>
        <div class="photo" style="margin-top:2.25rem;">
          <img src="/img/morning-cup.jpg" alt="A still morning: a warm cup in soft window light" width="960" height="640" loading="lazy" />
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- PANEL 4 · white · close -->
    <section class="panel center" style="padding-top:0;">
      <div class="container narrow">
        <h3>Start here</h3>
        <p>You don't have to explain it perfectly. Bring the thing your mind won't put down.</p>
        <a href="/get-started" class="btn" style="margin-top:0.5rem;">Get Started</a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</Base>
